    <p>All-Day Book Sale</p>
    <p>Or­gan­ised by arts plat­form Grey Projects, the book sale will raise funds to help sus­tain the free men­tal health coun­selling ses­sions it is run­ning for cul­tural work­ers af­fected by the pan­demic. Check out the art, phi­los­o­phy, photograph­y and de­sign books that are go­ing for $4 or $8.</p>
    <p>The com­pany is also ac­cept­ing book do­na­tions to­day from 1 to 7pm. WHERE: Grey Projects, 6B Kim Tian Road MRT: Tiong Bahru</p>
    <p>WHEN: To­mor­row, 11am - 6pm AD­MIS­SION: Free</p>
    <p>INFO: www.greypro­jects.org/events</p>
    <p>How To Fall In Love With Clas­sics (Sci­ence Fic­tion): The Left Hand Of Dark­ness By Ur­sula K. Le Guin</p>
    <p>The 1969 sci­ence-fic­tion novel is a cos­mic ad­ven­ture that takes hu­mankind to the frozen planet of Win­ter. An en­voy finds his mis­sion tricky and per­ilous when he is baf­fled that the planet’s na­tives are am­bi­sex­ual and have no fixed sex. Poet, graphic artist and lit­er­ary critic Gwee Li Sui will ex­pand on the idea of rad­i­cal dif­fer­ence in an in­ti­mate re­la­tion­ship, which has be­come one of the story’s ma­jor lessons.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Pub­lic Li­braries Sin­ga­pore Face­book Live WHEN: Thu, 7pm AD­MIS­SION: Free INFO: bit.ly/2H3vRz1</p>


